author: Inside Edition
description: At this wedding, the first dance was in a pool. Edward La Rue met Marlene Parsons in a water aerobics class at their local YMCA. When they got engaged, pool director Alie Morgan, who just happens to be an ordained minister, offered to marry them in a pool. For the big day, Parsons wore a traditional veil and a tutu with a corset on her T-shirt. La Rue sported a long-sleeve tuxedo T-shirt with a top hat.  Their guests wore their best swimsuits.
title: This Newlywed Couple Has Their First Dance In A Pool

author: Inside Edition
description: These robbery suspects returned stolen goods. In 2024, a man and woman helped themselves to Christmas decorations in Long Beach, California, right across the street from a church. In October, a man coming out of a gas station took off in a car with a baby in the backseat. In 2016, after stealing a wallet, a thief had the nerve to criticize its victim with a rude note when they returned the items. Inside Edition Digital's Andrea Swindall has more.
title: Robbery Suspects Who Returned The Goods
